    "Another way A view affirmed and used in the Prolog-centric (and hence only extensional) and pedagogically oriented tour through thinking as reasoning in the study mentioned in Levesque .",
    "The lead author, along with author P. Bello, is, in addition, convinced not only that an agent's perception of its internal, mental environment is equally important, but also working on formalizing and implementing the relationship between internal perception (which calls for its own intensional operator in cognitive calculi) and reasoning.",
    "For an exploration of internal to put our goal of integration is to say that it is aimed at unifying \"bands of cognition.\"",
